# Changelog

This file is managed by `semantic-release`.

Releases are created automatically from commits pushed to `main` when at least one commit matches a releasable type.

Release rules:
- `feat` -> minor release
- `fix` -> patch release
- `perf` -> patch release
- `revert` -> patch release
- `BREAKING CHANGE` or `type!:` -> major release

Non-releasable commits such as `docs`, `chore`, `ci`, `test`, `style`, and `refactor` do not create a tag unless they include a breaking change marker.

Tags use the format `vX.Y.Z`.

The first generated release entry will appear here after the first successful release run on `main`.
